Four persons are feared dead after a fatal motor accident in Toro, on the Jos-Bauchi express road on Friday evening, while many sustained varying degrees of injury. The accident, DAILY POST learned, occurred due to the heavy rainfall witnessed in parts of Bauchi State. It was gathered that two Opel Vectra cars on opposite directions had a head on collision, leading to the death of the deceased. DAILY POST was informed that the four people who lost their lives in the fatal accident are businessmen, selling goods in Bauchi Central Market in Bauchi metropolis. Unconfirmed reports claim that many other persons also lost their lives and scores of properties destroyed after the heavy rainfall. As of the time of filing this report, there has not been any official statement from concerned authorities.